    <item>
      <title>Does one have to be a genius to do maths?</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 14 May 2007 01:01:11 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;does-one-have-to-be-a-genius-to-do-maths&#34;&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do maths?&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Better beware of notions like genius and inspiration; they are a sort of magic wand and should be used sparingly by anybody who wants to see things clearly.&#xA;(José Ortega y Gasset, &amp;ldquo;Notes on the novel&amp;rdquo;)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Does one have to be a genius to do mathematics?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Work hard</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/work-hard/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 06 May 2007 18:52:08 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/work-hard/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/work-hard.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    https://terrytao.wordpress.com/career-advice/work-hard/&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;work-hard&#34;&gt;Work hard&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;blockquote&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Every mathematician worthy of the name has experienced … the state of lucid exaltation in which one thought succeeds another as if miraculously… this feeling may last for hours at a time, even for days. Once you have experienced it, you are eager to repeat it but unable to do it at will, unless perhaps by dogged work…&lt;/em&gt; (&lt;a href=&#34;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andr%C3%A9_Weil&#34;&gt;André Weil&lt;/a&gt;, “The Apprenticeship of a Mathematician”)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>The Princeton Companion to Mathematics</title>
      <link>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/the-princeton-companion-to-mathematics/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/orig/the-princeton-companion-to-mathematics/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://linguage.github.io/terencetao/career-advice/zh/the-princeton-companion-to-mathematics.zh/&#34;&gt;中文版本&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;div&#xA;  class=&#34;link-card group relative my-3 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-[var(--lc-border,rgba(15,23,42,0.12))] bg-[var(--lc-bg,var(--card-bg,var(--surface,#ffffff))))] transition-shadow duration-150 hover:shadow-[var(--lc-shadow-hover,0_14px_30px_-18px_rgba(15,23,42,0.35))]&#34;&#xA;  data-url=&#34;http://press.princeton.edu/titles/8350.html&#34;&#xA;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;a&#xA;    class=&#34;link-card__fallback block px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--lc-url,var(--link-color,#0e6a85))] underline-offset-4 hover:underline&#34;&#xA;    href=&#34;http://press.princeton.edu/titles/8350.html&#34;&#xA;    target=&#34;_blank&#34;&#xA;    rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&#xA;  &gt;&#xA;    http://press.princeton.edu/titles/8350.html&#xA;  &lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h1 id=&#34;the-princeton-companion-to-mathematics&#34;&gt;The Princeton Companion to Mathematics&lt;/h1&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Edited by &lt;a href=&#34;https://press.princeton.edu/taxonomy/term/18984&#34;&gt;Timothy Gowers&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://press.princeton.edu/taxonomy/term/18985&#34;&gt;June Barrow-Green&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://press.princeton.edu/taxonomy/term/18986&#34;&gt;Imre Leader&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ultimate mathematics reference book&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;https://pup-assets.imgix.net/onix/images/9780691118802.jpg?w=410&amp;amp;auto=format&#34; alt=&#34;&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is a one-of-a-kind reference for anyone with a serious interest in mathematics. Edited by Timothy Gowers, a recipient of the Fields Medal, it presents nearly two hundred entries—written especially for this book by some of the world’s leading mathematicians—that introduce basic mathematical tools and vocabulary; trace the development of modern mathematics; explain essential terms and concepts; examine core ideas in major areas of mathematics; describe the achievements of scores of famous mathematicians; explore the impact of mathematics on other disciplines such as biology, finance, and music—and much, much more.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
